modules.description: Provides primitives for managing delimited continuations and effect handlers, including capture, shift, and reset operations. Works with continuation tokens, effect records, and control flow structures specific to OCaml 5's effect system. Used to implement non-local control flow in cooperative multitasking or domain-specific languages.

Provides operations for managing delimited continuations and prompts, including creating prompts, capturing and invoking subcontinuations, and resetting execution contexts. Works with prompt and subcontinuation types to enable non-local control flow. Used for implementing backtracking, coroutines, and custom exception handling within specific scopes.
